threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered downloader. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ASCII text, with no line terminators

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The code first changes the current directory to a temporary location. It then downloads a remote file named `apps.bin` from a specified HTTPS URL, saving it locally as `update`. Following the download, it attempts to remove any extended attributes from the `update` file, suppressing any potential error messages. Subsequently, it grants execute permissions to the `update` file and proceeds to execute it.
